snippet.textDisplay:
One of my biggest fears ive been trying to get over is me being scared to meet new people, not knowing what will happen what this person will think of me or if they're good people at all. But over the last year the seek discomfort motto has pushed me to try get out of this, I went to Seoul, South Korea in the summer and the people I met along with the experience I had travelling alone was life changing. Because of this I've fallen in love with travel, my new found long lost passion that I want to persue, I now want to get out there and meet new people, yes I still struggle with opening up to people but I'm not gonna let that stop me and that helped by the influence of these 3 brilliant guys, who through me watching their videos I was inspired to face my fear and in turn found a new part of myself.

P.S. I doubt this will been seen by many people but if anyones in Brighton, UK I'll be glad to meet up and get to know you. I'm a student at the nearby Uni.❤
snippet.textOriginal:
One of my biggest fears ive been trying to get over is me being scared to meet new people, not knowing what will happen what this person will think of me or if they're good people at all. But over the last year the seek discomfort motto has  pushed me to try get out of this, I went to Seoul,  South Korea in the summer and the people I met along with the experience I had travelling alone was life changing. Because of this I've fallen in love with travel, my new found long lost passion that I want to persue, I now want to get out there and meet new people, yes I still struggle with opening up to people but I'm not gonna let that stop me and that helped by the influence of these 3 brilliant guys, who through me watching their videos I was inspired to face my fear and in turn found a new part of myself.

P.S. I doubt this will been seen by many people but if anyones in Brighton, UK I'll be glad to meet up and get to know you. I'm a  student at the nearby Uni.❤

snippet.textDisplay:
Seek discomfort to me means to do that thing anyway like type it anyway, write it, go for it anyway even if you think or know that no one will see or acknowledge it. It's doing things for the sake of doing them and not worrying about anything else. Additionally (as a perfectionist), it's also allowing myself to not be super duper great at things I do. It's allowing myself the space to learn and become better at something, and learning to love the process.
Starting uni in 2020, here's to new experiences and personal growth!

snippet.textDisplay:
I met a girl a year ago who lives on the other side of the world from me. This April, will be my first trip out to her home country to see her in person. Throughout the year I’ve known her, I’ve fallen in love. She’s the most special person I’ve ever had the pleasure of meeting. Such a hardworking, kind, funny, patient and loveable soul.

I’m nervous and excited to see her for the first time, but not only will I be seeing the love of my life for the first time... but I’ll be traveling to a whole different country thousands of miles away from my home country, alone. That’s gonna be one of the craziest things I’ve ever done. I’m so stoked, a little impatient, anxious but most importantly excited beyond anything I’ve ever been excited for.

Just wanted to share. Thanks for reading. ❤️
